cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with depth estimation using neural networks and defocus blur. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves the use of a realistic model of blur variation with respect to depth, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The use of neural networks for depth estimation also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of a new dataset, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper deals with image processing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
